 :tx/rationale "STEERING-LOOP ITEM 2 — EMBEDDER-AWARE THRESHOLD: JOIN_THRESHOLD=0.20 is calibrated for model2vec cosine distribution [0.15-0.40], but hash embedder needs ~0.65 (sparse binary-like distribution). A store that starts with hash (no model) and later gets model2vec has a threshold wrong for one or both. ROOT CAUSE: The threshold is a property of the METRIC SPACE (embedder), not the DOMAIN (project). Two projects using the same model should use the same threshold. Two models on the same project should use different thresholds. This is NOT a C9 violation — it's a function of the embedder, not policy. FIX: Add join_threshold() method to TextEmbedder trait with default 0.65. HashEmbedder returns 0.65. Embedder returns 0.20. observe.rs reads from embedder, policy config can still override. VERIFICATION: Hash-only store uses 0.65. Model store uses 0.20. No concept assignment failures from threshold mismatch. INTERACTION: Prerequisite for correct behavior without model. Independent of naming fix."
